<article>
    <h1>Ne&#xAD;ti&#xAD;zens scram&#xAD;ble to caption Gor&#xAD;don-Le&#xAD;vitt&#x2019;s FB post of a S&#x2019;pore scene</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200810/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-10"><time>2020-08-10</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE</span>
        - <span role="byline">Chelsea Kiew</span>
    </section>

    <p>Hollywood ac­tor Joseph Gor­donLe­vitt (right) re­cently drew ex­cite­ment among ne­ti­zens in Sin­ga­pore af­ter post­ing a photo on Face­book.</p>
    <p>Posted last Sunday, it shows a woman in a colour­ful dress. Car­ry­ing a pink bag and trans­par­ent um­brella, she seems to be danc­ing bare­foot in the rain in the Sin­ga­pore heart­land (above).</p>
    <p>Gor­don-Le­vitt, 39, who has 5.9 mil­lion fol­low­ers on Face­book, wrote in the caption, “Any writ­ers around?”, en­cour­ag­ing fans to “tell the story of this scene in only one sen­tence”.</p>
    <p>And fans, ex­cited to see a photo taken in Sin­ga­pore on the FB page of the ac­tor, quickly posted their take.</p>
    <p>One wrote: “I don’t care that I’m bare­foot but I’m sure as hell not get­ting my new Laboutins (sic) wet as I wait for my cab – I’ll put them back on when in the car.”</p>
    <p>Another, Sin­ga­porean po­et­writer Joshua Ip, wrote: “Sin­ga­pore: Pas­sion Made Pos­si­ble.”</p>
    <p>The post has gath­ered more than 390 shares and close to 2,000 in­ter­ac­tions.</p>

